definitions.definition: Emphasizes the truth of an assertion made to contradict an evidently false assumption held by the listener.
examples: — Sian sia , nearby here don’t have library. — The National Library is a five-minute walk from here what , no meh ?

definitions.definition: Used to invite agreement or acknowledgment when something is assumed to be straightforward or already obvious to begin with; similar in function to “ right ?” and “ as you know ” .
examples: If it doesn’t get sunlight, it won’t grow what , so you should consider moving it closer to the window.

definitions.definition: Used after a direct assertion to reinforce a disagreeing opinion.
examples: The lava cakes are not that bad what .
